(5001, 3878, '_wp_attached_file', '2013/11/UNICEF-RDC-2013-Morton-ECHO-RRMP1.jpg'),
(5002, 3878, '_wp_attachment_metadata', 'a:5:{s:5:"width";i:612;s:6:"height";i:408;s:4:"file";s:45:"2013/11/UNICEF-RDC-2013-Morton-ECHO-RRMP1.jpg";s:5:"sizes";a:2:{s:9:"thumbnail";a:4:{s:4:"file";s:45:"UNICEF-RDC-2013-Morton-ECHO-RRMP1-150x150.jpg";s:5:"width";i:150;s:6:"height";i:150;s:9:"mime-type";s:10:"image/jpeg";}s:6:"medium";a:4:{s:4:"file";s:45:"UNICEF-RDC-2013-Morton-ECHO-RRMP1-300x200.jpg";s:5:"width";i:300;s:6:"height";i:200;s:9:"mime-type";s:10:"image/jpeg";}}s:10:"image_meta";a:10:{s:8:"aperture";i:0;s:6:"credit";s:12:"Brett Morton";s:6:"camera";s:0:"";s:7:"caption";s:0:"";s:17:"created_timestamp";i:1376648921;s:9:"copyright";s:25:"© UNICEF RDC/2013/Morton";s:12:"focal_length";i:0;s:3:"iso";i:0;s:13:"shutter_speed";i:0;s:5:"title";s:1123:"On August 16, 2013 UNICEF and Merlin, with the support of ECHO and UNHASS delivered 3.5 tons of medical/nutritional supplies to Nobili, North Kivu, DRC, as part of the OCHA/UNICEF led RRMP program. Following attacks on Kamongo by the ADF-Nalu rebels in July, more than 66,000 people were displaced from their homes in to surrounding villages in DRC and neighboring Uganda. RRMP assessments in late July revealed a 550% increase in child mortality and nearly 50% prevelance of diarrhea in children under 5. With many displaced settling in Nobili, approximately 9 km from Kamongo, the population more than tripled from 8,500 residents to 30,500. The hosiptal and health centers were looted during the attacks, leaving little resources to combat disease and malnutrition. Immediately following the distribution of supplies Merlin opened mobile health clinics in the area and began support to the hospital and area health centers, and together with UNICEF, the Ministry of Health and Lutheran World Federation (LWF) began a five-day measles vaccination campaign targeting more than 45,000 displaced and host-community children.";}}'),
(5003, 3881, '_wp_attached_file', '2013/10/UNICEF-DRC-2013-Morton-ECHO-RRMP-NFI-Fair1.jpg'),
(5004, 3881, '_wp_attachment_metadata', 'a:5:{s:5:"width";i:629;s:6:"height";i:420;s:4:"file";s:54:"2013/10/UNICEF-DRC-2013-Morton-ECHO-RRMP-NFI-Fair1.jpg";s:5:"sizes";a:2:{s:9:"thumbnail";a:4:{s:4:"file";s:54:"UNICEF-DRC-2013-Morton-ECHO-RRMP-NFI-Fair1-150x150.jpg";s:5:"width";i:150;s:6:"height";i:150;s:9:"mime-type";s:10:"image/jpeg";}s:6:"medium";a:4:{s:4:"file";s:54:"UNICEF-DRC-2013-Morton-ECHO-RRMP-NFI-Fair1-300x200.jpg";s:5:"width";i:300;s:6:"height";i:200;s:9:"mime-type";s:10:"image/jpeg";}}s:10:"image_meta";a:10:{s:8:"aperture";i:0;s:6:"credit";s:12:"Brett Morton";s:6:"camera";s:0:"";s:7:"caption";s:0:"";s:17:"created_timestamp";i:1382619555;s:9:"copyright";s:25:"© UNICEF RDC/2013/Morton";s:12:"focal_length";i:0;s:3:"iso";i:0;s:13:"shutter_speed";i:0;s:5:"title";s:995:"The ECHO-funded UNHAS helicopter departs Kasika, Mwenga Territory.\n\n__\n\nThe IASC Emergency Directors Group visit humanitarian activities in Mwenga, Territory, South Kivu, Democratic Republic of the Congo on Thursday, October 24, 2013.\n\nWith numerous armed confrontations continuing in eastern DRC, more than 2.7 million are currently displaced. The visit of Emergency Directors, including OCHA Operations Director John Ging and UNICEF Director of Emergency Programs Ted Chaiban, among others, is meant to help create a shared understanding of challenges within the various humanitarian agencies present, as well as to help identify solutions to operational gaps. \n\nTraveling by ECHO-funded helicopter to Kasika, Mwenga, the Directors delegation visited an ECHO-funded Food Fair implemented by AVSI, a FAO-funded food security project, a health center supported by UNICEF carrying out support to malnourished children, as well as a food distribution funded by WFP and implemented by World Vision.";}}'),
