(2375, 1, '2013-12-06 15:42:41', '2013-12-06 15:42:41', '', 'Children gather to observe the start of the three-day national vaccination campaign in the Mugunga 1 Internal Displacement Camp, North Kivu, DRC.Together with representatives of the DRC Ministry of Health, the WHO and local partners, UNICEF launched the North Kivu portion of the three-day National Polio Vaccination Campaign on July 11th at the Mugunga 1 Internal Displacement Camp outside Goma. Country-wide the vaccination campaign aims to immunize 16.3 million children aged 0-5 years against Polio, taking the occasion to also provide Vitamin A supplementation and deworming pills to the children and register children under 3 months with the civil authorities. Within North Kivu Province, the campaign has set out to immunize 1.3 million children.Since the launch in 1988 of the Global Initiative to Eradicate Polio, coordinated by the governments of countries concerned, WHO, UNICEF, Rotary International and the CDC-Atlanta, the 350,000 children paralyzed annually by Polio has been reduced by more than 99% while reducing the number of endemic countries from 125 to 3. Participating in the immunization campaigns since 1998, the DRC has seen a steady reduction of polio cases, and has now been polio-free since December 2011.', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'children-gather-to-observe-the-start-of-the-three-day-national-vaccination-campaign-in-the-mugunga-1-internal-displacement-camp-north-kivu-drc-together-with-representatives-of-the-drc-ministry-of', '', '', '2013-12-06 15:42:41', '2013-12-06 15:42:41', '', 2374, 'http://staging.ponabana.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/36.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
