llow beneficiaries to select goods and supplies according to their own priorities, leading to improved efficiency in NFI assistance and as well as greater participation of affected populations. Operating in essence as a local market, beneficiaries are given cash vouchers, which vendors can then redeem for cash following the closure of the fair. The participating households are free to choose the items which will serve them best, while the local economy is reinforced through the participation of local vendors. This ?Fair Approach? represented more than 50% of RRMP NFI distributions in 2012, and is scheduled to account for 60% in 2013.Agathe, 30, fled her home in Mwimbili village in February when fighting broke out between the Raia Mutomboki and FARDC. After returning briefly in March, she fled again with her husband and three children in April, seeking shelter with a host family in Mwenga Center. ?I?m really content with what I purchased,? Agathe explained of the basins, saucepans and clothing she purchased at the fair. ?Most importantly, I can now prepare food for the family.?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'march-16-2013kionvu-mwenga-south-kivu-drcunicef-rrmp-partner-avsi-carries-out-nfi-fair-since-late-2012-fighting-between-rebels-of-the-raia-mutomboki-and-the-congolese-army-fardc-has-lead-t', '', '', '2013-12-07 11:30:12', '2013-12-07 11:30:12', '', 2465, 'http://staging.ponabana.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/201.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
