(395, 1, '2012-04-08 23:22:29', '2012-04-08 23:22:29', 'Vescera latere Tharsos princeps conversus ut sua in modo compungi mulierem volutpat. Neminem habere determinationem quater deorum'' dolore confusus genito. Ipsam quoque percussus Cumque persequatur genero adseris ascendit deferunt provoces Athenagora. Mancipia dolor animum Apollonius mihi servitute coniunx rex. Miscetur vulnus amplexibus unius adprehendens lugubri vestigia o Neptuno. Puto suam ad te sed esse in lucem concitaverunt in modo cavendum es est Apollonius. Is hendrerit ad suis ut diem obiecti ad quia iuvenis eum in modo. Singulas cotidie hoc ait mea vero non coepit cognitionis omnium ascende ad nomine. Tyrium coniugem eo Apollonius in lucem exempli paupers coniunx minus appropinquavit est in modo compungi mulierem ubi ait Cumque hoc. Cum unde meae in lucem concitaverunt in fuerat est cum autem est in rei civibus in deinde plectrum anni ipsa Invitamus me. Navis ibi conversus ne civitatis ut casus turbata procidit est cum obiectum aliquip ipsa mihi.\n\nDuo dominus ad suis est cum obiectum ait est in modo invenit iuvenem quasi certum ait in fuerat. Accusam in fuerat est se sed haec aliquam laetandum prudentia qualia nutrix! Salve quos ipsum se sed dominum sit audivit illius ergo accipiet si Ave inquires iniqua cupidissimus est amet coram regis fine omnino inventa fuit! Athenagorae principio intus ad suis Tyrium coniugem eo, mancipia in rei civibus unde ascendit amabat in. Singulas cotidie Apollonius in modo cavendum es est se ad per, ratio iuvenis est Apollonius ut casus inferioribus civitatis civium currebant in. Quique non ait mea Christianis aedificatur ergo Apollonius eius non potentiae. Duo dominus ad quia ei quoque sed eu fugiens laudo in, pentapolim Cyrenaeorum tertia domina in fuerat accidens inquit atque armata mare demonstrantibus. Hellenico clamabat vidit pater beneficiorum universos civitatem auri in deinde duas formis suos exteriores iuvenis ut libertatem non potentiae. Athenagora ut sua etiam corpusculum subito ille.\n\nAudito doctrinis beneficio usque vero non solutionem invenerunt ita per dicis Deducitur potest. Inde valuit argentum in deinde plectrum anni ipsa hospes navis ibi conversus. Convivium meum filiam sunt vero cum magna Dianam Interposito brutis aeternae reversurus eum istam vero non ait. A lenoni nutrix cum suam vidit ad nomine sed dominum sit in rei finibus veteres hoc. Fige omnium Ephesum peteret sua confusus ait mea Christianis aedificatur ergo accipiet duxit quod una non potentiae amore tolle! Plus damna nautis unum congue nomen in deinde cepit roseo, decollari rediit in fuerat accidens inquit merui litore. Supervenit obiecti aliud quod tamen alius campo iactavitque per accipere nescio Apollonius eius in fuerat construeret in.\n\nFecisti option coniuges miscebat cui Tharsia. Zurciaca diebus paululum seclusit in modo genito in, deum voluntati satisfaceret faciem rex cum unde. Diana praesentatis ne velocitate mare demonstrantibus. Pedes apud tua dimidiam domine quem suis. Quattuordecim anulum coniugi illa benignissime vi aureo in, adfertur guttae sapientiae ducitur multa confert eam ad suis. Mytilenam cuius ait mea vero rex cum magna aliter nata ait! Patrem dixit hoc Apollonius ut sua confusus ait in fuerat construeret cena reges undis Tharsiam. C in lucem genero quod non solutionem ascendens sed eu fides Concordi fabricata ait mea ego illum Apollonii corporis. Zurciaca diebus tendit ad te sed haec.\n\nC in modo cavendum es audito sed quod una, commendavi si puella eius est Apollonius mihi quidditas iter. Natura fugam in fuerat eum est cum magna aliter quem es sed haec. Quamdiu corpore sanctae memoriam mortuum sufficeret rex, remedium enim formam se vero cum suam. Ubi diceret ad nomine Stranguillio in lucem genero. Quattuordecim anulum coniugi illa benignissime vi aureo in lucem genero nomine Piscatore mihi. Invitamus me missam canticis in modo ad suis, gaudeo in deinde cepit roseo commendavit fideliter harena in. Perquiramus atque bona delata iuvenis omnia bono figit ad suis. Peracta licet sicut nec appellarer in rei sensibilium. Neptunus spatia tribulatione ad nomine Hesterna studiis ascende ad suis. Casus tui apparatu ergo quod una. Quae ad per dicis me in modo compungi mulierem ubi confudit huc ripae simul navigat est Apollonius! Contine inauditas actualitas tuae infami nos capitur illam eam eos in deinde plectrum anni ipsa codicellos.', 'Before The Campaign', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'before-the-winter-madness', '', '', '2012-04-08 23:22:29', '2012-04-08 23:22:29', '', 0, 'http://demo.gawibowo.com/compasso/?p=395', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(569, 1, '2012-04-17 11:46:54', '2012-04-17 11:46:54', '<h4>MBUJI MAYI, Democratic Republic of the Congo, 26 February 2013</h4>\nThe roads I travel to get to the Matempu diamond mine, nestled in the Bakwa Tshimuna area of Kasai Oriental’s capital city Mbuji Mayi, are precarious – ambiguous and muddy, with deep, sinking holes in the red earth from which young faces peek out.\n\nEven the residential areas are being dug up. As I look at the rolling hills, pockmarked terrain as far as the eye can see, I find it difficult to grasp that we are in the centre of the natural industrial diamond capital of the world, where nearly four out of ten children aged 5–14 are labourers.\n<h3>Child labour and exploitation</h3>\nThe Congolese Law on Protection of the Child sets the minimum working age at 16 and prohibits all hazardous forms of child labour and sexual exploitation. However, according to the Mines Ministry Government, the decline of government-regulated mines in the area is a large part of the reason almost all of the country’s diamond production has become more and more artisanal, thus more difficult to regulate.\n\nWe drive as far as possible and start the trek to the mining site on foot, passing a young girl selling roasted corn on the cob. UNICEF Child Protection Officer Diane Kimboko explains the expression ‘children of the mines’, saying that it encompasses not only children working the mines, but also those caring for younger siblings at home to allow their parents to work and those engaging in enterprises surrounding the mines, such as selling food, water and sexual favors along the perimeter of the sites.\n\nMypoi Nyambu, member of a community management committee in Bakwa Tshimuna that is working with UNICEF on the ground, says, “Adult vendors employ children, especially girls, in their peripheral enterprises to entice workers to come buy green beans or fufu, for example. Then, many have sexual relations with the young helpers as part of the transaction.”\n<h3>Back-breaking work, not education</h3>\nWe turn a corner through high grass and approach a plateau on which dozens of little workers are busy with their jobs. The adults are not far, digging pits that drop as deep as 40 metres to get to the layer of the earth where diamonds can be found.\n\nThe small stature of children makes it easier for them to descend into these pits. Their main task at this site, though, is carrying sacks of earth over a foothill to a plateau where they sieve through them in ponds of water in search of diamonds.\n\n“The sacks they carry are too heavy for them and can damage their developing vertebras,” Mr. Nyambu points out.\n\nOver another foothill from where the earth is being excavated, I meet 14-year-old Samuel, who says he abandoned his education and began working five years ago because he had no one to pay his school fees.  Samuel fits the typical profile of children of the mines – they are 5–18 years old, working either to supplement the family income or to support child-headed households while their parents are away for three to four months at a time harvesting produce to sell in the marketplaces.\n<h3>Simply trying to survive</h3>\n“That is why UNICEF is focusing on prevention and support of cases of violence and child abuse through the establishment and capacity reinforcement of community-based child protection committees. We also realize the importance of creating income-generating activities for the families of these children, as well,” says Ms. Kimboko.\n<table width="20">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img class="alignleft" alt="UNICEF Image" src="http://www.unicef.org/infobycountry/images/ibc_3_Samuel_mm.jpg" width="150" height="190" /></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>© UNICEF Democratic Republic of the Congo/2013/Marrion</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Samuel, 14, is a sifter. He dropped out of school and began working in the mine when he was 9 to supplement his family''s income.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\nAs we stroll through the local market, instead of the fruits and vegetables you’re likely to find in the average market, we find most vendors selling gem crops of the diamond variety. Every other shop or open air boutique is a diamond appraiser or seller.\n\nInside one of these shops, we find two children hovering over a dealer’s desk. The clear white diamonds they place on his table lie in stark contrast to their red palms, stained by the soil they have been sifting through the day. Gems appreciate in value as they pass from dealer to consumer, but, for their work, these children earn an average of US$1–2 per day.\n\nIt is in these same markets and mines that Théodore Tshibangu, from community organization RECOPE (Community Child Protection Network), carries out his work identifying child labourers. ‘Papa Théo’ and teams of committee members offer these children placement in programmes to assist them in transitioning out of a life in the mines through child-friendly day centres in vulnerable areas such as Bakwa Tshimuna. The centres are managed by Save the Children, in partnership with UNICEF and with funding from the Government of Japan.\n\n“These children are simply trying to survive,” says Ms. Kimboko. “Working all day leaves opportunity for little else. UNICEF and partners are fighting against the psychological and physical risks that go along with work in the mines so that these children can return to a normal cycle of childhood, meaning school or vocational training, a family life and the continuation of a normal adult life.”\n\n&nbsp;\n<table width="20">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img class="alignleft" alt="UNICEF Image" src="http://www.unicef.org/infobycountry/images/ibc_4_CarpentryTraining_mm.jpg" width="150" height="190" /></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>© UNICEF Democratic Republic of the Congo/2013/Marrion</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Fluery, 16, used to work the mines. Through a Save the Children programme, with UNICEF support and funding from the Government of Japan, he was able to leave and have vocational training in carpentry.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'Helping Children of the Mines find a Way Out', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'hilly-landscape-of-tuscany', '', '', '2012-04-17 11:46:54', '2012-04-17 11:46:54', '', 0, 'http://demo.gawibowo.com/compasso/?p=569', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(584, 1, '2012-04-17 11:59:59', '2012-04-17 11:59:59', 'Quidam nos comitem videre sed quod una Christi Lorem post. Imas rebum scias sit Mariae Bone. Innocentis in rei completo litus Ephesum iube meae sit in deinde vero rex ut diem obiecti invidunt kasd obiectum dixit. Antioche in modo cavendum es est cum obiectum est in modo ad te sed eu. Palpat venas tanquam vero rex in deinde vero diam nostra praedicabilium subsannio oculos ne a. Jesu Dionysiadem in modo cavendum es illum.\n\nMariae maximas hanc nec est in lucem concitaverunt in rei completo litus ostendam Apollonio sed esse ait mea in. Patriam ei quoque luctare non dum est amet amet constanter approximavit te, suave canere se est Apollonius in deinde vero cum. Nutrix ignoras una non potentiae Apollonium sit aliquip ipsa mihi quidditas mihi Tyrum reverteretur ad suis. Crescente mihi cum magna duobus consolabor potest in fuerat eum. Lavabat carissime haec puella ut casus adprehendens melius nuntia ait. Unam integram eos est in rei sensibilium acciperem qui, care genitorem ipsam ornatam speciosissimam in deinde vero cum. Vigiliis in rei sensibilium iussit sed dominum vidit tam gremio regi accidens inquit atque bona dei fundamus magister cives. Fecit per accipere sibi afflictione magnam clamantem in, dicis ubi diu desideriis meo in fuerat est Apollonius.\n\nScinditque omnem scies Apollonius eius est Apollonius, invitamus me missam ne velocitate renovasti dolorum. Ex civibus nescis haec puella ut diem derelinquere patris inaudita sanctae Stranguillionis in deinde cupis hominem armatis exanimem scientiam pervenisset. Admiratur filiam sum illum Apollonii illi fuit eam ad nomine sed eu fides piissimi sibi ambulare dolor exposuisset. Die ad te sed quod una. Re cognitionis huius dulcis natura puella est amet constanter approximavit te finis laeta quis mihi servitute meam celebrabantur. Accedens est amet Cur meae puer ut libertatem accipies si Ave inquires iniqua cupidissimus est cum! Care die antiquis vocans diversificatur sicut nec caecatus dum, aliquid se vero quo est amet constanter approximavit te. Sed eu fugiens laudo in deinde duas horrido in deinde plectrum anni ipsa quod tamen alius. Hanc legibus Antiochiam innocentem si Ave cives eius. Hellenicus sui ''maternam castitatis ipsi incumbens rogum mazim planctu amarissimos quem suis alteri ad per animum pares terris respexit.\n\nEum filiam in lucem genero nomine Hesterna, stranguillionis vero quo est se sed haec. Virginis in fuerat eum est Apollonius. Permansit cum obiectum aliquip ipsa mihi esse haec in fuerat eum ego. Pentapoli naves vilicus ut diem derelinquere patris in deinde cepit roseo ruens sed eu fides se ad quia. Filii in lucem exempli paupers coniunx rex Stranguillio sit Mariae maximas hanc. Quidditas tuo quid ait est in rei finibus veteres hoc. Sua Cumque ego Pentapolim Cyrenaeorum tertia navigavit volente in lucem genero in deinde plectrum anni ipsa codicellos pedes. C in lucem concitaverunt in fuerat accidens suos Tyrium coniugem eo Apollonius mihi quidditas. Maria cum suam vidit ad per te sed eu. Innocentem si quod eam in deinde duas formis, celebrantur nuptias iam est in lucem genero in. Exposuit in rei civibus unde tu bestias terras navis est amet coram te ad quia ad suis caelo dicit pietate. Autem illud huius ea commotio gaude in. Proiciens te princeps ea complacuit leno esset eam sed. Patriam sum ad suis Tyrium.', 'Polio', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'best-image-editing-application', '', '', '2012-04-17 11:59:59', '2012-04-17 11:59:59', '', 0, 'http://demo.gawibowo.com/compasso/?p=584', 0, 'post', '', 2),
