(5050, 1, '2014-01-17 08:08:24', '2014-01-17 08:08:24', '', 'The ECHO-funded UNHAS helicopter departs Kasika, Mwenga Territory.__The IASC Emergency Directors Group visit humanitarian activities in Mwenga, Territory, South Kivu, Democratic Republic of the Congo on Thursday, October 24, 2013.With numerous armed confrontations continuing in eastern DRC, more than 2.7 million are currently displaced. The visit of Emergency Directors, including OCHA Operations Director John Ging and UNICEF Director of Emergency Programs Ted Chaiban, among others, is meant to help create a shared understanding of challenges within the various humanitarian agencies present, as well as to help identify solutions to operational gaps. Traveling by ECHO-funded helicopter to Kasika, Mwenga, the Directors delegation visited an ECHO-funded Food Fair implemented by AVSI, a FAO-funded food security project, a health center supported by UNICEF carrying out support to malnourished children, as well as a food distribution funded by WFP and implemented by World Vision.', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-echo-funded-unhas-helicopter-departs-kasika-mwenga-territory-__the-iasc-emergency-directors-group-visit-humanitarian-activities-in-mwenga-territory-south-kivu-democratic-republic-of-the-co-2', '', '', '2014-01-17 08:08:24', '2014-01-17 08:08:24', '', 0, 'http://staging.ponabana.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/UNICEF-DRC-2013-Morton-ECHO-RRMP-NFI-Fair1.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
