(4227, 1, '2014-01-28 10:07:20', '2014-01-28 10:07:20', '<strong>Naomi. UNICEF-AVSI Child Friendly Space. January 23, 2014. </strong>\n\nAs part of the UNICEF, WFP and UNHCR Deputy Executive Director''s visit to eastern DRC the delegation traveled to the Mugunga 3 Internally Displaced Persons (IDP) Camp outside Goma, North Kivu. After visiting a school and health center, the delegates had the chance to visit a UNICEF-supported Child Friendly Space (CFS). Operated by UNICEF partner AVSI, the CFS is a place where children can gather outside of school hours to participate in recreational and psychosocial activities in a protected environment.\n\nHome to approximately 15,000 IDPs, more than 1,000 displaced children gather each day at the Mugunga 3 CFS. Trained supervisors guide children aged 3-18 in age-specific activities ranging from pre-school learning activities to educational games, discussion groups and vocational trainings.\n\n<strong>FROM THE PHOTOGRAPHER: </strong>\n\nAmidst the controlled-chaos of the thousand-plus children in the CFS this day, Naomi was playing a game with other girls whereby the goal was to collect as many of the other girls shoes as possible before being tagged with a soft, fabric ball. In a moment of calm, she stopped directly in front of me and posed for a brief moment with this smile you see. Though most of the children aren''t still for long enough for me to do justice with the photos, one sees countless moments like this each day at the CFS.\n\n&nbsp;', 'Photo of the week - 25 January 2014', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'photo-of-the-week-25-january-2014', '', '', '2014-01-28 10:07:20', '2014-01-28 10:07:20', '', 0, 'http://ponabana.com/?p=4227', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(4307, 1, '2014-01-28 16:39:27', '2014-01-28 16:39:27', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://staging.ponabana.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/IMG_674811.jpg">\n</a>Mon nom est Bora Kaumba je suis enfant reporter de Lubumbashi. J''ai 14 ans et j''envisage d''être Criminologue.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://staging.ponabana.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/IMG_674811.jpg"><img class="alignright" alt="IMG_6748" src="http://staging.ponabana.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/IMG_674811.jpg" width="160" height="201" /></a>Etre enfant reporter pour moi est une façon de rencontrer plusieurs personnalités, d’être au service des enfants, de la population et de connaitre l''opinion, la vie, la perspective, la pensée et les atouts des enfants du Katanga.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Comme nous ne pouvons pas avoir les yeux partout, il faut que nous soyons le plus nombreux possible à exprimer nos points de vue lorsque nos droits ne sont pas respectés.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">C''est pour cela que j''ai créé un groupe sur Facebook où j''invite tous les enfants reporters de RDC et du monde entier à nous rejoindre pour se connaître, échanger et trouver des solutions ensemble!</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Vous retrouverez ce groupe à cette adresse:</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/1397094947210451/" target="_blank">https://www.facebook.com/groups/1397094947210451/</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Si vous n''êtes pas déjà amis avec la page Bana RD Congo, vous pouvez aussi nous rejoindre sur:</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/bana.rdcongo.75#" target="_blank">https://www.facebook.com/bana.rdcongo.75#</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Plus on sera nombreux et plus notre droit à la participation sera mis en avant. </strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Merci ! On est ensemble!!!</strong></p>\n&nbsp;', 'Un groupe Facebook pour tous les Enfants Reporters de RDC !', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'une-page-facebook-pour-tous-les-enfants-reporters-de-rdc', '', '', '2014-01-28 16:39:27', '2014-01-28 16:39:27', '', 0, 'http://ponabana.com/?p=4307', 0, 'post', '', 2),
