(5176, 2, '2014-02-16 16:19:06', '2014-02-16 16:19:06', '[one_half] <strong>Main key statistic on the situation of DRC''s children.</strong>\r\n\r\nIn this section you will find essential data to better apprehend the context, the progresses that have been made ​​and the way forward to ensure that all children''s rights are respected in the DRC.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[/one_half]\r\n\r\n[one_half_last]\r\n\r\n[accordion]\r\n\r\n[section title="Main key statistics"] Key data on the progresses towards the Millennium Development Goals as well as the situation of children in the DRC in a single document[/section]\r\n\r\n[section title="Education"]<a href="/?page_id=2437">M</a>ain key statistics on Education[/section]\r\n\r\n[section title="Health"]Main key statistics on Health[/section]\r\n\r\n[section title="Nutrition"]<a href="/?page_id=2484">Main key statistics on Nutrition</a>.[/section]\r\n\r\n[section title="Protection"]Main key statistics on<a href="/?page_id=2387"> Protection</a>.[/section]\r\n\r\n[section title="Emergencies"]Main key statistics on Emergencies.[/section]\r\n\r\n[/accordion] [/one_half_last]', 'Key Statistics', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3385-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-16 16:19:06', '2014-02-16 16:19:06', '', 3385, 'http://staging.ponabana.com/?p=5176', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(5177, 2, '2014-02-16 16:21:33', '2014-02-16 16:21:33', '<img class="alignleft" alt="2" src="http://ponabana.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/2-300x199.jpg" width="300" height="199" />\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The water and sanitation sector is weakened by a fragmented political structure. There are currently 6 different government bodies implicated, through 6 separate ministries. Major agencies include: REGIDESO for urban water (Ministry of Energy); National Hydraulic Service for rural water (SNHR), Ministry of Rural Development; PNA for sanitation (Ministry of the Environment) and the 9th Bureau of the Ministry of Health working in both water and sanitation. To facilitate the coordination of the water and sanitation sector, a separate agency, the CNAEA, was created in the 1990s and is based at the Ministry of Planning.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Support was given to the National Committee for Action on Water and Sanitation under the Ministry of Plan (CNAEA), for DRC to join 35 other countries as members of the Sanitation and Water for All initiative. The Government committed at the Washington high level conference in April 2012 to strengthen WASH institutions and related human resources in 2013-2014. UNICEF participates in the WASH Donor Group and the Hygiene Thematic Group. Among the priorities promoted by UNICEF are to push for support to the government strategy on the elimination of cholera in endemic and epidemic areas.</p>', 'Water and Sanitation - Key Challenges in DRC', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3370-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-16 16:21:33', '2014-02-16 16:21:33', '', 3370, 'http://staging.ponabana.com/?p=5177', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(5178, 2, '2014-02-16 16:21:49', '2014-02-16 16:21:49', '<a href="http://ponabana.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/ZAI_Mbandaka_23-March-2011-307.jpg"><img alt="ZAI_Mbandaka_23 March 2011 307" src="http://ponabana.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/ZAI_Mbandaka_23-March-2011-307.jpg" width="640" height="475" /></a>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>IMPROVE WATER SUPPLY AND SANITATION</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In DRC as in many countries around the world, UNICEF is working to improve water supply and sanitation in schools and communities and to promote hygienic practices . We support multiple and diverse activities and cooperate with many partners, including families, communities, governments and organizations sharing the same values.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>INTERVENTION IN EMERGENCIES</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We provide emergency assistance to communities and people at risk of not being supplied with water and threatened by disease emergency. All programs of UNICEF''s water and sanitation are designed to contribute to the achievement of the Millennium Development Goals related to water and sanitation : reduce, by 2015, the proportion of people without sustainable access to safe water and basic sanitation.</p>', 'Water and Sanitation', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3357-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-16 16:21:49', '2014-02-16 16:21:49', '', 3357, 'http://staging.ponabana.com/?p=5178', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(5179, 2, '2014-02-16 16:22:17', '2014-02-16 16:22:17', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://ponabana.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/110921095256.jpg"><img class="alignleft" alt="110921095256" src="http://ponabana.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/110921095256-242x300.jpg" width="242" height="300" /></a>DRC is not on track to reach the Millennium Development Goals (MDGs) in water and sanitation. The achievement of Goal 7 would require reaching 72% access to drinking water and 58% access to improved sanitation by 2015. Currently 47% of the population has access to safe drinking water (83% urban and 31% rural), while only 14% of the population has access to adequate sanitation facilities (36% urban and 4% rural) according to MICS 2010. Thus to meet the MDGs 17.5 million people in DRC would need to gain access to water and 30.8 million people must gain access to sanitation by 2015.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>MAIN KEY STATISTICS</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>-</strong> <strong>47 %</strong> of the total population has access to safe drinking water, and <strong>14%</strong> access to improved sanitation (MICS 2010).</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">- In rural areas, water coverage is <strong>31 %</strong>; rural improved sanitation <strong>4%</strong> (MICS 2010).</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">- In addition, there are cholera epidemics in endemic cholera prone zone every year in the provinces of Katanga, Oriental, North and South Kivu. DRC is also facing outbreaks in non-endemic areas along the river Congo or cross border with Zambia/Congo Brazzaville. In August 2013, 21 264 cholera cases with 321 deaths have been reported in total and half of them came from Katanga Province and cross-border with Zambia (2014 HNO).</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">- <strong>2.7 millions of IDP’s</strong> are facing challenges to meet their right to get access to safe water, improved sanitation and hygiene</p>', 'Water and Sanitation - Key statistics', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3365-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-16 16:22:17', '2014-02-16 16:22:17', '', 3365, 'http://staging.ponabana.com/?p=5179', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(5180, 2, '2014-02-16 16:22:32', '2014-02-16 16:22:32', '<img alt="NYHQ2000-0682" src="http://ponabana.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/UNI35078.jpg" />\r\n\r\n<strong> 4 MILLION PEOPLE WILL GAIN ACCESS TO IMPROVED WATER AND SANITATION SERVICES BY 2017</strong>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The UNICEF Country Programme 2013-2017 extended the Healthy Villages and Schools program to almost 6,000 villages and 1,500 schools, the equivalent of approximately 4 million people gaining first-time access to improved WASH services.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">By September 30, 2019, UNICEF planned to reach 7500 villages which will have committees acting to protect and maintain their healthy environment</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The HVHS programme is scaling up to be operational in 250 out of the 515 Health Zones (49%). The second phase of the Healthy Villages and Schools program is focusing on sustainability, including the sustainability of hardware WASH installations; institutional capacity, accountability and obligation, health outcomes, and the scalability of quality results. A strategy is being defined to promote complementarity between the programme and projects of other government institutions, NGOs or the private sector.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">To promote transition between emergency and development, new strategies are under discussion within the different stakeholders. UNICEF is also supporting the 2013-2017 New Multisectoral Strategic Plan for the Elimination of Cholera in DRC.</p>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Water and Sanitation - The way forward in DRC', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3361-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-16 16:22:32', '2014-02-16 16:22:32', '', 3361, 'http://staging.ponabana.com/?p=5180', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(5183, 2, '2014-02-16 16:23:51', '2014-02-16 16:23:51', '[one_third]\r\n\r\n<strong>Pona Bana is the UNICEF DRC team''s blog.</strong>\r\n\r\nHere our team of bloggers and partners share their experiences of working on the ground and their passion for children''s rights in the DRC.\r\n\r\nReports, key figures, programme documents, topical articles, photos, videos and graphics, you can find out everything about the situation of children in the DRC and how we are working with our partners to ensure that their rights are respected.\r\n\r\n[/one_third]\r\n\r\n[one_third]\r\n\r\n<strong>"Voices of Children” </strong>\r\n\r\nWe are convinced that as the main beneficiaries of our work, children should be consulted, heard and taken into account.\r\n\r\nA forum will soon be set up for children to exchange their ideas, where regular <a href="/?cat_ID=122">articles</a>, <a href="/?cat_ID=121">cartoons </a>and <a href="http://www.youtube.com/user/unicefrdc2012?feature=watch">videos </a>will be posted.\r\n\r\n[/one_third]\r\n\r\n[one_third_last]\r\n\r\n<strong>Your Participation</strong>\r\n\r\nYour views and opinions are important to us.\r\n\r\nPlease do not hesitate to ask our specialists any questions you may have, to comment on our articles or tell us about your ideas, concerns or suggestions. This blog aims to continuously improve and be enhanced by adapting to your needs.\r\n\r\nTogether, we can build a better future for the children of the DRC!\r\n\r\n[/one_third_last]', 'Who are we?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3760-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-16 16:23:51', '2014-02-16 16:23:51', '', 3760, 'http://staging.ponabana.com/?p=5183', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
